Author: joshwa
Title: C.E.O. Libraries Reveal Keys to Success - New York Times

Author: dpapathanasiou
Content:
So it starts well:

There's no difference between code and data

but then none of his examples actually show that in action.

Instead, he does a bunch of simple iterations and print statements; most people would look at that and say, "I can do that with [language x]".

Author: tiki12revolt
Content: Utility may count more (I would tend to agree with that), but at least some people will wonder why one product works 'so much better' than all the rest when it just came out of the woodworks.
